                807.5
            ],
            "ignore": false,
            "order": 4,
            "anno_id": 1,
            "text": " In an alternative accretion geometry, the so-called lamppost geometry, a point corona lies above the black hole which illuminates the accretion disk. If the precession of the disk is the proposed mechanism to produce the LFQPO under this accretion geometry (Schnittman et al. 2006), the modulation in the Compton component at high energy band (say, e.g., above 100 keV) is not expected unless the corona is partially obscured by the precessing disk.",
            "line_with_spans": [
                {
                    "category_type": "text_span",
                    "poly": [
                        172.5,
                        507.5,
                        1187.5,
                        507.5,
                        1187.5,
